commitResults.messageBody:
NUS Module Planner stores user information about past semesters but does
not include a convenient way to access commonly-needed summary
information such as the total MCs a user is doing in the current
semester or the users current Cumulative Average Points (CAP).

The lack of these convenience functions means that users will have to
manually compute this information, which could be easily computed by NUS
Module Planner for them instead.

Lets include two simple commands corresponding to each of the above
summary statistics by creating two new comands `show cap` and `show
mcs`.

Keeping the format of these commands simple makes remembering them easy.
